Alpha PRD — Status as of 2026-03-02

This file summarizes what has been implemented for the alpha version and what remains, per the MASTER-PRD-2402 and alpha scope.

---

WHAT HAS BEEN DONE

Discover feed
• Non-functional search bar removed; feed uses full width.
• Map entry is a single floating teal pill (map icon) bottom-right; feed content extends to bottom of screen (no gray/white box).
• Map pill is hidden when any detail view is shown (event, spot, or collection).
• Feed list and background extend into bottom safe area so the feed goes all the way down.

Save (Flow 1 — Find)
• Unified save control: small gray capsule with bookmark icon + save count; turns teal/green when saved. Same style on cards and detail screens.
• Save works from: event cards, spot cards, map event preview, event detail (hero only), spot detail (hero only), collection detail (hero), and individual spot rows inside a collection.
• Save count updates in place after toggle (events, spots, collection spots); backend save/unsave is wired.

First-run / location
• First-run city behavior: app prompts for location permission; if denied or unavailable, fallback is Stockholm (not Manhattan). AppConfig has fallbackLatitude/Longitude for Stockholm.

Map view
• Map uses full screen height; filter row is a floating card (categories “hang freely”) with spacing so the arrow/recenter isn’t cramped.
• Close (X) removed from top; Discover pill (compass icon) bottom-right dismisses map and returns to Discover.
• Event preview save button uses same capsule style and updates count.

Detail pages (event, spot, collection)
• Event detail: single save pill on hero (top right of photo); “FRIENDS WHO SAVED THIS” with mutuals row (avatars + count/names). Redundant “Add to Collection” / second save pill in body removed.
• Spot detail: single save pill on hero; redundant save pill in body removed. Save state and count come from feed/view model when opened from Discover.
• Collection detail: “Collection” label removed from above the collection name on the hero. Orange numbered badges (1, 2, 3) removed from spot cards. Tags on collection spot cards limited to discover filter categories only (Food, Drinks, Music, Art, Markets, Community). Save buttons on individual spots in a collection are wired to API (saved state + count load and update).

