UI/UX CHECKS (BEFORE RELEASE)

• Run a full UI/UX pass to ensure consistency and that the app looks good:
  – Save button: same capsule style (gray → teal when saved, bookmark + count) everywhere it appears.
  – Typography, spacing, and colors (e.g. portal primary, muted, cards) consistent across Discover, Map, and Profile.
  – Detail screens: no duplicate actions (e.g. only one save control per screen where we removed redundancy).
  – List and scroll views: no stray gray/white bars; content and background extend to edges/safe areas as intended.
  – Map: floating controls (filters, Discover pill) clearly tappable and not overlapping content in a confusing way.
  – Accessibility: labels and identifiers in place where we added them; verify VoiceOver and dynamic type where relevant.

